glosses: To strive for, to struggle for.
To work hard or continuously on something.

etymology: Inherited from Ottoman Turkish اوغراشمق (uġraşmak, “to struggle or fight with another or one another, to strive hard at something”), from Ottoman Turkish اوغرامق (uġramak, “to go to, through or by a place, to meet, to encounter”), from Proto-Turkic *ugra- (“to meet, to go to meet, to intend”), morphologically uğra- + -ş + -mak.
